tools: sys.exec, sys.write, sys.http.get, sys.read, sys.ls
description: Deploys a storybook

Perform the following actions including subtasks.

1. Ensure ansible is installed using pipenv
2. Create an inventory file for ubuntu@xxxx.amazonaws.com
3. Create a playbook for installing and starting apache
4. Run the playbook against the host. Make sure to use pipenv run.
5. Verify that the host is serving web requests
6. Create a webpage using the contents of the public/stories directory in a new directory called dist.
7. Copy images from public/stories to the appropriate location in dist. Update the image references if needed.
8. Create a playbook to deploy the site in dist
9. Run the playbook against the webserver
